						h4 Description
						p Cheatsheet is for the little things you never remember: hotel rooms, license plates, luggage combination, ID numbers. Write them down in Cheatsheet and then refer to them anytime in a Widget or paste them anywhere with the Custom Keyboard. No more fumbling to unlock your phone and find your notes app; Cheatsheet is as easy as looking at your lock screen, pulling up the keyboard, or glancing at your Apple Watch.
						
						ul
							h6 App Features:
							li Simple UI for adding and managing your cheats.
							li Over 200 icons to help you recognize what you’re looking for.
							li Quickly copy a cheat by tapping-and-holding on a row.
							li Search for your cheats, both in the app and in Spotlight.
							li Use Shortcuts or Siri to “add notes to Cheatsheet” or “find notes in Cheatsheet”.
							li Organize your cheats with folders and titles.
							li Protect your cheats with Passcode Lock (Pro feature).
							li Sync between all your iOS devices via iCloud (Pro feature).
						
						ul
						 h6 Widgets:
						 li Multiple sizes, styles, and colors.
						 li Tap a cheat to open it. Tap the “+” button to add a cheat in the app.
						 li Action widget enables one-tap options to copy text, delete a note, or open a link.
						 li Cheatsheet also has a “Today widget” on iOS 17 and older.

						ul
							h6 Apple Watch:
							li Add, edit, and delete cheats right from your wrist.
							li Complication shows your top cheat right on your watch face.
							li Syncs to your iPhone via iCloud (Pro feature).

						ul
							h6 iOS Keyboard Extension:
							li Shows up to 50 cheats, which you can insert anywhere you can use a custom keyboard.
							li Includes space, delete, and return keys to help with simple edits.

						ul
							h6 Advanced Features:
							li Automate your workflows with Shortcuts.
							li  Action extension: send text or URLs to Cheatsheet from any app via the share sheet.
							li  Customize the Cheatsheet widget’s appearance and behavior to suit your needs.
							li  Add or open notes from Control Center (iOS 18 required).
							li  URL scheme for adding a cheat: cheatsheet://add?text=everything%20is%20awesome.

						ul
							h6 Cheatsheet Pro:
							li Remove limits on the widget, keyboard, and Watch app.
							li Protect your cheats with Passcode Lock.
							li Organize your cheats with folders.
							li Sync your cheats between your devices with iCloud. 
							li Cheatsheet Pro is a simple, annual subscription. Cheatsheet for Mac is sold separately.
							li Purchases help support the ongoing development of Cheatsheet. :)

						p Cheatsheet is available in English, Dutch, French, German, Hindi, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese, Russian, Simplified Chinese, and Spanish.
						
						p Cheatsheet has a 4.7-star rating with over 5,000 reviews worldwide. Cheatsheet has been featured in TechCrunch, Gizmodo, 9to5Mac, MacRumors, TechRadar, and Macworld.

